headline: CBRE Q2 Deep Dive: Resilient Business Segments and Leasing Drive Outperformance
summary: Commercial real estate firm CBRE (NYSE:CBRE) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 16.2% year on year to $9.75 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.19 per share was 11.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
